snippet.textDisplay:
Dana upping MGregor's confidence with Cerrone, whom McGregor can blaze past through with ease. Judging from his mannerism in this interview, he looks pretty humbled, hands on the waist usually is a sign of uneasy and feeling of defenselessness. No trashtalking, no trying to sell fights, Khabib really did open a whole lotta dimension to him. He got beat down and dismantled on that fight, everyone will agree.

But here's the thing. I fear this version of Notorious more. If he's methodical and calculated before, expect him to be more surgical and polished this time. If he was a math whiz before the Khabib fight, I think this time he upgraded to surgeon status with the way he'll approach the game, knowing mistakes and miscalculations are really costly - not only can he lose that fight, but his confidence as well

snippet.textDisplay:
Could he actually be back?
Could Conor McGregor actually be back to the mindset that brought him his successes?

I really hope so, because the Conor that he became was an utter moron! He became distracted with all the classic hangups, Money, Fame, Notoriety and self Godhood.

If he has sincerely rediscovered the humble, self awareness he so desperately needs to have, then the world could very well be about to get a fantastic 2020 and perhaps more.

Conor, don't let yourself & your team down again.

Loss is nothing, Lose with humility and dignity and you will still be a winner.

Victory in itself is nothing if the same is not attached with it. But, win like a true champion should win and the world is yours my man..........

Go get them fu**ers! 😁

Could he actually be back? 
Could Conor McGregor actually be back to the mindset that brought him his successes? 

I really hope so, because the Conor that he became was an utter moron! He became distracted with all the classic hangups, Money, Fame, Notoriety and self Godhood. 

If he has sincerely rediscovered the humble, self awareness he so desperately needs to have, then the world could very well be about to get a fantastic 2020 and perhaps more. 

Conor, don't let yourself & your team down again. 

Loss is nothing, Lose with humility and dignity and you will still be a winner. 

Victory in itself is nothing if the same is not attached with it. But, win like a true champion should win and the world is yours my man..........

Go get them fu**ers! 😁
